No one knows how the Shambler came to be, one day it just seemed to appear.  It
is made up of a pile of rotting leaves, decomposing wood, and putrid vines that
stands ten feet tall.  Two moldy, quivering stumps hang from its sides, slimy
roots flailing wildly about.  It has no legs, instead moving like a slug,
leaving a trail of thick, green-tinted slime.
~
